node.text:
Explorer/Activist Johan Ernst Nilson. Nilson has climbed the Seven Summits (and many other peaks), visited 178 countries and some of the most remote places on Earth, and he is in the Guinness Book of World Records for his Three Poles Challenge Expedition. His travels and experiences have allowed him to see climate change and its consequences first hand, and now Nilson is an activist for change, leading people on expeditions, giving talks, and making films about the environment.

node.text:
The Astronomia Everest project started with renowned Swedish explorer and environmental activist @johanernst taking an Astronomia Tourbillon with him on an expedition to the Himalayas.
"I wore the regular Astronomia Tourbillon on my last climb to the Himalayas, where I went up to 6,200 meters (almost 20,000 feet), in -30 C degree, extreme conditions," Nilson says. "You would think that such a complicated watch would be delicate and fragile, but it isn't, and it performed perfectly in all conditions. I used it climbing up ice walls, with my ice ax, banging it against rock and ice and it held up extremely well.”

Push the right-hand crown of the incredible BUGATTI Chiron Tourbillon and the engine comes to life – the crankshaft turns and the 16 pistons pump up and down, just like BUGATTI’S iconic W16 engine. Two “turbochargers” on the side of the engine block spin while the engine runs, adding to the visual impact.
Incredible to see and unbelievably complicated to realize (the movement is comprised of 578 components), the BUGATTI Chiron Tourbillon timepiece seamlessly marries engines and watches – something no other watchmaker has done before.

The Astronomia Everest project started with renowned Swedish explorer and environmental activist @johanernst taking an Astronomia Tourbillon with him on an expedition to the Himalayas.
"I wore the regular Astronomia Tourbillon on my last climb to the Himalayas, where I went up to 6,200 meters (almost 20,000 feet), in -30 C degree, extreme conditions," Nilson says. "You would think that such a complicated watch would be delicate and fragile, but it isn't, and it performed perfectly in all conditions. I used it climbing up ice walls, with my ice ax, banging it against rock and ice and it held up extremely well.”

Explorer/Activist Johan Ernst Nilson. Nilson has climbed the Seven Summits (and many other peaks), visited 178 countries and some of the most remote places on Earth, and he is in the Guinness Book of World Records for his Three Poles Challenge Expedition. His travels and experiences have allowed him to see climate change and its consequences first hand, and now Nilson is an activist for change, leading people on expeditions, giving talks, and making films about the environment.

In the world of watchmaking, the presence of a tourbillon in a watch’s movement places the piece among the elite. @JacobandCo’s Twin Turbo Furious 300+ sets itself apart from this rarified group, incorporating two accelerated triple axis tourbillons into its striking design. The tourbillons work to compensate for the effects of gravity on the precision of the movement.⠀ ⠀
⠀
Even the case of the Twin Turbo Furious Bugatti 300+ is super complicated – made of forged carbon, with a titanium core to ensure water resistance - the case alone is comprised of 88 parts. The grand complication movement is made up of 832 individual parts – incredible to consider that many parts coming together, and amazing to see in action.⠀

node.text: Jacob & Co. produces experiences that are as innovative, disruptive, and enduring as its groundbreaking timepieces. This includes an official Jacob & Co. “Swiss” passport. This bright red document available in seven languages provides everything you need to accompany your new Swiss-made Jacob & Co. timepiece. It serves as a personal token of our appreciation that you have chosen to take a journey where centuries old Swiss watchmaking tradition meets bold, contemporary ingenuity. #jacobandco

node.text: To enhance the experience of owning a Jacob & Co. timepiece, the luxury brand’s founder, Jacob Arabo, created a “Swiss” passport that accompanies all new watches. About the size of a wallet, it provides all the details that you need to keep your Swiss-made timepiece in top condition. It serves as yet another innovative way for Jacob & Co. to present something truly unique for its clients. #jacobandco

node.text: The timing mechanisms and the on-demand oil derrick automaton of the Jacob & Co. Oil Pump Black DLC timepiece are powered by manual winding JCAM33 caliber with a double-axis tourbillon that rotates in 60 seconds and 2.5 minutes. The dial base is a grill evocative of oil rigs. The oil derricks come to life on demand with a push of button placing further emphasis on the pipes, barrel, and power reserve in the form of an oil pressure gauge that make up the oil industry themed timepiece.#jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JACOB & CO. in Jacob & Co. with @jacobandco. May be an image of wrist watch.

node.text: The Oil Pump Black DLC timepiece brings the traditional automaton into the 21st century while celebrating the pioneering spirit of the oil industry. The dial display of two moving oil derricks and a system of pipes, barrels, and a power reserve in the form of an oil pressure gauge are clearly visible inside a 49.5mm crystal sapphire and titanium black DLC case. The automaton comes to life on demand by pushing an 18K rose gold button at 2 o’clock.#jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JACOB & CO. in Jacob & Co. with @jacobandco. May be an image of wrist watch.

node.text: The Oil Pump Black DLC timepiece celebrates the oil business with an on-demand automaton in the dial that takes you straight to the oil fields. Activating the 18k rose gold pusher at 2 o’clock starts two 18k rose gold plated derricks that move up and down as if they are pumping oil. There’s also an18k rose gold oil barrel and pipelines; and a power reserve indicator at 3 o’clock that looks like an oil pressure gauge.#jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie

Conceived by Jacob & Co. and high-performance auto manufacturer, Bugatti, the Bugatti Chiron tourbillon is a timepiece with functions that have never appeared on a watch before or since. Its sleek black titanium case reveals a fully working Bugatti W16 engine suspended by four screws that look like shock absorbers. The iconic Bugatti horseshoe grille reveals a one-minute flying tourbillon on a 30-degree angle. The power reserve at 9 o’clock replicates a gas pump. It all comes together for a sleek, dynamic, and groundbreaking auto-themed timepiece. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie #bugatti #bugattichiron

node.text: Building a fully working automotive engine, a one-minute flying tourbillon inclined at a 30-degree angle, and several other components of aesthetic and technical mastery, and placing them inside a tonneau-shaped watch is a horological achievement. The Bugatti Chiron timepiece is a tribute to the hyper sportscar of the same name. It replicates the high-performance automobile, not only in its appearance, but in its fine design and high watchmaking craftsmanship. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie #bugatti #bugattichiron

node.text: After a year of development, @bugatti and Jacob & Co. created the Bugatti Chiron Tourbillon, a watch unlike no other. The tonneau-shaped case of the Bugatti Chiron Tourbillon is inspired by the flowing lines of the Chiron hyper sportscar, giving it a sleek, aerodynamic appearance. Beneath the sapphire crystal is a fully working Bugatti W16 car engine that operates on demand. It’s a groundbreaking concept that emulates the speed and beauty of the Chiron. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie #bugatti #bugattichiron

node.text: 💎 New Launch 💎 Finding approximately 390 blue sapphires of varying shades is challenging. Fortunately, Jacob & Co.’s long-term relationships with the gem industry paid off. The sapphires were sourced and then cut and polished to match a predetermined color pattern. These stones are also sourced without inconclusions and with what the trade refers to as “eye to loupe clean” quality. Sourcing the stones took nearly eight months. It took another seven weeks for a craftsman to invisibly set the sapphires for a smooth finish. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie

node.text: 💎 Introducing💎 The bridges of the JCAA43 automatic caliber for the Blue Camo Caviar are invisibly set with 338 round diamonds that are visible through the sapphire crystal caseback. The same care it took to source, cut, and set the blue sapphires throughout the front of the watch went into the diamonds on the movement. So, no matter how you view this watch, there is the sparkle of gem-set brilliance. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie

node.text: 💎New Launch 💎 From every angle, the Blue Camo Caviar shows it brilliance. Approximately 390 blue sapphires of different hues are invisibly set to the case, lugs, and dial of this timepiece. The color pattern was created through computer-aided design prior to sourcing the stones. The blue sapphires were sourced to match this pattern. However, when rough sapphire is cut and polished the shade may change, adding to the complexity. The answer was to source more sapphires needed to account for color changes and breakage. The result is a watch with the rich, lustrous translucence of the finest caviar. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie
